msgstr "``GenericAlias`` ਆਬਜੈਕਟਾਂ ਦੇ ਖਾਸ ਗੁਣ (Attributes)"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6040
msgid "All parameterized generics implement special read-only attributes."
msgstr ""
"ਸਾਰੇ parameterized generics ਖਾਸ ਸਿਰਫ਼-ਪੜ੍ਹਨਯੋਗ (read-only) attributes "
"ਲਾਗੂ ਕਰਦੇ ਹਨ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6044
msgid "This attribute points at the non-parameterized generic class::"
msgstr ""
"ਇਹ attribute non-parameterized generic class ਵੱਲ ਸੰਕੇਤ ਕਰਦਾ ਹੈ::"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6046
msgid ""
">>> list[int].__origin__\n"
"<class 'list'>"
msgstr ""
">>> list[int].__origin__\n"
"<class 'list'>"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6052
msgid ""
"This attribute is a :class:`tuple` (possibly of length 1) of generic types "
"passed to the original :meth:`~object.__class_getitem__` of the generic "
"class::"
msgstr ""
"ਇਹ attribute generic class ਦੇ ਅਸਲ :meth:`~object.__class_getitem__` ਨੂੰ "
"ਪਾਸ ਕੀਤੀਆਂ generic ਕਿਸਮਾਂ ਦੀ ਇੱਕ :class:`tuple` ਹੁੰਦੀ ਹੈ (ਜਿਸ ਦੀ ਲੰਬਾਈ 1 "
"ਵੀ ਹੋ ਸਕਦੀ ਹੈ)::"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6056
msgid ""
">>> dict[str, list[int]].__args__\n"
"(<class 'str'>, list[int])"
msgstr ""
">>> dict[str, list[int]].__args__\n"
"(<class 'str'>, list[int])"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6062
msgid ""
"This attribute is a lazily computed tuple (possibly empty) of unique type "
"variables found in ``__args__``::"
msgstr ""
"ਇਹ attribute ``__args__`` ਵਿੱਚ ਮਿਲਣ ਵਾਲੇ ਵਿਲੱਖਣ type variables ਦੀ ਇੱਕ "
"lazy ਤਰੀਕੇ ਨਾਲ ਗਿਣੀ ਗਈ tuple ਹੈ (ਜੋ ਖਾਲੀ ਵੀ ਹੋ ਸਕਦੀ ਹੈ)::"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6065
msgid ""
">>> from typing import TypeVar\n"
"\n"
">>> T = TypeVar('T')\n"
">>> list[T].__parameters__\n"
"(~T,)"
msgstr ""
">>> from typing import TypeVar\n"
"\n"
">>> T = TypeVar('T')\n"
">>> list[T].__parameters__\n"
"(~T,)"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6073
msgid ""
"A ``GenericAlias`` object with :class:`typing.ParamSpec` parameters may not "
"have correct ``__parameters__`` after substitution because :class:`typing."
"ParamSpec` is intended primarily for static type checking."
msgstr ""
":class:`typing.ParamSpec` parameters ਵਾਲੇ ``GenericAlias`` object ਵਿੱਚ "
"substitution ਤੋਂ ਬਾਅਦ ਸਹੀ ``__parameters__`` ਨਾ ਹੋ ਸਕਦੇ ਹਨ, ਕਿਉਂਕਿ "
":class:`typing.ParamSpec` ਮੁੱਖ ਤੌਰ 'ਤੇ static type checking ਲਈ ਬਣਾਇਆ ਗਿਆ ਹੈ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6080
msgid ""
"A boolean that is true if the alias has been unpacked using the ``*`` "
"operator (see :data:`~typing.TypeVarTuple`)."
msgstr ""
"ਇੱਕ boolean ਮੁੱਲ ਜੋ ``True`` ਹੁੰਦਾ ਹੈ ਜੇ alias ਨੂੰ ``*`` operator ਦੀ ਵਰਤੋਂ "
"ਕਰਕੇ unpack ਕੀਤਾ ਗਿਆ ਹੋਵੇ (ਵੇਖੋ :data:`~typing.TypeVarTuple`)।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6088
msgid ":pep:`484` - Type Hints"
msgstr ":pep:`484` - Type Hints"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6089
msgid "Introducing Python's framework for type annotations."
msgstr "Python ਦੇ type annotations framework ਦਾ ਪਰਿਚਯ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6091
msgid ":pep:`585` - Type Hinting Generics In Standard Collections"
msgstr ":pep:`585` - Type Hinting Generics In Standard Collections"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6092
msgid ""
"Introducing the ability to natively parameterize standard-library classes, "
"provided they implement the special class method :meth:`~object."
"__class_getitem__`."
msgstr ""
"Standard library classes ਨੂੰ native ਤੌਰ 'ਤੇ parameterize ਕਰਨ ਦੀ ਸਮਰੱਥਾ "
"ਦਾ ਪਰਿਚਯ, ਜੇਕਰ ਉਹ ਖਾਸ class method "
":meth:`~object.__class_getitem__` ਨੂੰ ਲਾਗੂ ਕਰਦੀਆਂ ਹੋਣ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6096
msgid ""
":ref:`Generics`, :ref:`user-defined generics <user-defined-generics>` and :"
"class:`typing.Generic`"
msgstr ""
":ref:`Generics`, :ref:`user-defined generics <user-defined-generics>` ਅਤੇ "
":class:`typing.Generic`"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6097
msgid ""
"Documentation on how to implement generic classes that can be parameterized "
"at runtime and understood by static type-checkers."
msgstr ""
"ਉਹ generic classes ਕਿਵੇਂ ਲਾਗੂ ਕੀਤੀਆਂ ਜਾਣ ਜੋ runtime 'ਤੇ parameterize "
"ਕੀਤੀਆਂ ਜਾ ਸਕਣ ਅਤੇ static type-checkers ਦੁਆਰਾ ਸਮਝੀਆਂ ਜਾ ਸਕਣ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6106
msgid "Union Type"
msgstr "Union Type"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6112
msgid ""
"A union object holds the value of the ``|`` (bitwise or) operation on "
"multiple :ref:`type objects <bltin-type-objects>`.  These types are intended "
"primarily for :term:`type annotations <annotation>`. The union type "
"expression enables cleaner type hinting syntax compared to subscripting :"
"class:`typing.Union`."
msgstr ""
"ਇੱਕ union object ਕਈ :ref:`type objects <bltin-type-objects>` ਉੱਤੇ ਕੀਤੀ "
"``|`` (bitwise or) ਕਾਰਵਾਈ ਦਾ ਮੁੱਲ ਰੱਖਦਾ ਹੈ। ਇਹ ਕਿਸਮਾਂ ਮੁੱਖ ਤੌਰ 'ਤੇ "
":term:`type annotations <annotation>` ਲਈ ਵਰਤੀਆਂ ਜਾਂਦੀਆਂ ਹਨ। Union type "
"expression, :class:`typing.Union` ਦੀ subscription ਦੇ ਮੁਕਾਬਲੇ ਹੋਰ ਸਾਫ਼ "
"type hinting syntax ਪ੍ਰਦਾਨ ਕਰਦੀ ਹੈ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6119
msgid ""
"Defines a union object which holds types *X*, *Y*, and so forth. ``X | Y`` "
"means either X or Y.  It is equivalent to ``typing.Union[X, Y]``. For "
"example, the following function expects an argument of type :class:`int` or :"
"class:`float`::"
msgstr ""
"ਇੱਕ union object ਪਰਿਭਾਸ਼ਿਤ ਕਰਦਾ ਹੈ ਜੋ *X*, *Y* ਆਦਿ ਕਿਸਮਾਂ ਨੂੰ ਰੱਖਦਾ ਹੈ। "
"``X | Y`` ਦਾ ਅਰਥ ਹੈ X ਜਾਂ Y। ਇਹ ``typing.Union[X, Y]`` ਦੇ ਬਰਾਬਰ ਹੈ। "
"ਉਦਾਹਰਨ ਲਈ, ਹੇਠਾਂ ਦਿੱਤਾ function :class:`int` ਜਾਂ :class:`float` ਕਿਸਮ "
"ਦਾ argument ਉਮੀਦ ਕਰਦਾ ਹੈ::"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6124
msgid ""
"def square(number: int | float) -> int | float:\n"
"    return number ** 2"
msgstr ""
"def square(number: int | float) -> int | float:\n"
"    return number ** 2"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6129
msgid ""
"The ``|`` operand cannot be used at runtime to define unions where one or "
"more members is a forward reference. For example, ``int | \"Foo\"``, where ``"
"\"Foo\"`` is a reference to a class not yet defined, will fail at runtime. "
"For unions which include forward references, present the whole expression as "
"a string, e.g. ``\"int | Foo\"``."
msgstr ""
"``|`` operand ਨੂੰ runtime 'ਤੇ ਉਹ unions ਪਰਿਭਾਸ਼ਿਤ ਕਰਨ ਲਈ ਨਹੀਂ ਵਰਤਿਆ ਜਾ "
"ਸਕਦਾ ਜਿੱਥੇ ਇੱਕ ਜਾਂ ਵੱਧ members forward reference ਹੋਣ। ਉਦਾਹਰਨ ਵਜੋਂ, "
"``int | \"Foo\"``, ਜਿੱਥੇ ``\"Foo\"`` ਅਜੇ ਤੱਕ ਪਰਿਭਾਸ਼ਿਤ ਨਾ ਕੀਤੀ ਗਈ class "
"ਦਾ reference ਹੈ, runtime 'ਤੇ ਅਸਫਲ ਹੋਵੇਗਾ। Forward references ਵਾਲੇ unions "
"ਲਈ ਪੂਰੇ expression ਨੂੰ string ਵਜੋਂ ਲਿਖੋ, ਜਿਵੇਂ ``\"int | Foo\"``।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6137
msgid ""
"Union objects can be tested for equality with other union objects.  Details:"
msgstr ""
"Union objects ਦੀ ਹੋਰ union objects ਨਾਲ ਸਮਾਨਤਾ (equality) ਲਈ ਜਾਂਚ ਕੀਤੀ "
"ਜਾ ਸਕਦੀ ਹੈ। ਵੇਰਵਾ:"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6139
msgid "Unions of unions are flattened::"
msgstr "Unions ਦੇ unions ਨੂੰ ਸਮਤਲ (flatten) ਕਰ ਦਿੱਤਾ ਜਾਂਦਾ ਹੈ::"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6141
msgid "(int | str) | float == int | str | float"
msgstr "(int | str) | float == int | str | float"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6143
msgid "Redundant types are removed::"
msgstr "ਫ਼ਾਲਤੂ (redundant) ਕਿਸਮਾਂ ਹਟਾ ਦਿੱਤੀਆਂ ਜਾਂਦੀਆਂ ਹਨ::"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6145
msgid "int | str | int == int | str"
msgstr "int | str | int == int | str"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6147
msgid "When comparing unions, the order is ignored::"
msgstr "Unions ਦੀ ਤੁਲਨਾ ਕਰਦੇ ਸਮੇਂ ਕ੍ਰਮ (order) ਨੂੰ ਅਣਡਿੱਠਾ ਕੀਤਾ ਜਾਂਦਾ ਹੈ::"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6149
msgid "int | str == str | int"
msgstr "int | str == str | int"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6151
msgid "It creates instances of :class:`typing.Union`::"
msgstr "ਇਹ :class:`typing.Union` ਦੇ instances ਬਣਾਉਂਦਾ ਹੈ::"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6153
msgid ""
"int | str == typing.Union[int, str]\n"
"type(int | str) is typing.Union"
msgstr ""
"int | str == typing.Union[int, str]\n"
"type(int | str) is typing.Union"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6156
msgid "Optional types can be spelled as a union with ``None``::"
msgstr "Optional ਕਿਸਮਾਂ ਨੂੰ ``None`` ਨਾਲ union ਵਜੋਂ ਲਿਖਿਆ ਜਾ ਸਕਦਾ ਹੈ::"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6158
msgid "str | None == typing.Optional[str]"
msgstr "str | None == typing.Optional[str]"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6163
msgid ""
"Calls to :func:`isinstance` and :func:`issubclass` are also supported with a "
"union object::"
msgstr ""
"Union object ਨਾਲ :func:`isinstance` ਅਤੇ :func:`issubclass` ਦੀਆਂ calls ਵੀ "
"ਸਮਰਥਿਤ ਹਨ::"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6166
msgid ""
">>> isinstance(\"\", int | str)\n"
"True"
msgstr ""
">>> isinstance(\"\", int | str)\n"
"True"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6169
msgid ""
"However, :ref:`parameterized generics <types-genericalias>` in union objects "
"cannot be checked::"
msgstr ""
"ਹਾਲਾਂਕਿ, union objects ਵਿੱਚ "
":ref:`parameterized generics <types-genericalias>` ਦੀ ਜਾਂਚ ਨਹੀਂ ਕੀਤੀ "
"ਜਾ ਸਕਦੀ::"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6172
msgid ""
">>> isinstance(1, int | list[int])  # short-circuit evaluation\n"
"True\n"
">>> isinstance([1], int | list[int])\n"
"Traceback (most recent call last):\n"
"  ...\n"
"TypeError: isinstance() argument 2 cannot be a parameterized generic"
msgstr ""
">>> isinstance(1, int | list[int])  # short-circuit evaluation\n"
"True\n"
">>> isinstance([1], int | list[int])\n"
"Traceback (most recent call last):\n"
"  ...\n"
"TypeError: isinstance() argument 2 cannot be a parameterized generic"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6179
msgid ""
"The user-exposed type for the union object can be accessed from :class:"
"`typing.Union` and used for :func:`isinstance` checks::"
msgstr ""
"Union object ਲਈ user-exposed type ਨੂੰ :class:`typing.Union` ਤੋਂ ਪ੍ਰਾਪਤ "
"ਕੀਤਾ ਜਾ ਸਕਦਾ ਹੈ ਅਤੇ :func:`isinstance` ਜਾਂਚਾਂ ਲਈ ਵਰਤਿਆ ਜਾ ਸਕਦਾ ਹੈ::"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6182
msgid ""
">>> import typing\n"
">>> isinstance(int | str, typing.Union)\n"
"True\n"
">>> typing.Union()\n"
"Traceback (most recent call last):\n"
"  File \"<stdin>\", line 1, in <module>\n"
"TypeError: cannot create 'typing.Union' instances"
msgstr ""
">>> import typing\n"
">>> isinstance(int | str, typing.Union)\n"
"True\n"
">>> typing.Union()\n"
"Traceback (most recent call last):\n"
"  File \"<stdin>\", line 1, in <module>\n"
"TypeError: cannot create 'typing.Union' instances"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6191
msgid ""
"The :meth:`!__or__` method for type objects was added to support the syntax "
"``X | Y``.  If a metaclass implements :meth:`!__or__`, the Union may "
"override it:"
msgstr ""
"Type objects ਲਈ :meth:`!__or__` ਮੈਥਡ ਨੂੰ ``X | Y`` syntax ਦਾ ਸਮਰਥਨ ਕਰਨ "
"ਲਈ ਜੋੜਿਆ ਗਿਆ ਸੀ। ਜੇ ਕੋਈ metaclass :meth:`!__or__` ਨੂੰ ਲਾਗੂ ਕਰਦੀ ਹੈ, ਤਾਂ "
"Union ਇਸਨੂੰ override ਕਰ ਸਕਦਾ ਹੈ:"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6195
msgid ""
">>> class M(type):\n"
"...     def __or__(self, other):\n"
"...         return \"Hello\"\n"
"...\n"
">>> class C(metaclass=M):\n"
"...     pass\n"
"...\n"
">>> C | int\n"
"'Hello'\n"
">>> int | C\n"
"int | C"
msgstr ""
">>> class M(type):\n"
"...     def __or__(self, other):\n"
"...         return \"Hello\"\n"
"...\n"
">>> class C(metaclass=M):\n"
"...     pass\n"
"...\n"
">>> C | int\n"
"'Hello'\n"
">>> int | C\n"
"int | C"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6211
msgid ":pep:`604` -- PEP proposing the ``X | Y`` syntax and the Union type."
msgstr ":pep:`604` -- ``X | Y`` syntax ਅਤੇ Union type ਦਾ ਪ੍ਰਸਤਾਵ ਕਰਨ ਵਾਲਾ PEP।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6217
msgid ""
"Union objects are now instances of :class:`typing.Union`. Previously, they "
"were instances of :class:`types.UnionType`, which remains an alias for :"
"class:`typing.Union`."
msgstr ""
"ਹੁਣ Union objects :class:`typing.Union` ਦੇ instances ਹਨ। ਪਹਿਲਾਂ ਇਹ "
":class:`types.UnionType` ਦੇ instances ਹੁੰਦੇ ਸਨ, ਜੋ ਅਜੇ ਵੀ "
":class:`typing.Union` ਦਾ ਇੱਕ alias ਹੈ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6224
msgid "Other Built-in Types"
msgstr "ਹੋਰ Built-in ਕਿਸਮਾਂ"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6226
msgid ""
"The interpreter supports several other kinds of objects. Most of these "
"support only one or two operations."
msgstr ""
"Interpreter ਕਈ ਹੋਰ ਕਿਸਮਾਂ ਦੇ objects ਦਾ ਸਮਰਥਨ ਕਰਦਾ ਹੈ। ਇਨ੍ਹਾਂ ਵਿੱਚੋਂ "
"ਜ਼ਿਆਦਾਤਰ ਕੇਵਲ ਇੱਕ ਜਾਂ ਦੋ operations ਦਾ ਹੀ ਸਮਰਥਨ ਕਰਦੇ ਹਨ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6233
msgid "Modules"
msgstr "ਮੋਡੀਊਲ"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6235
msgid ""
"The only special operation on a module is attribute access: ``m.name``, "
"where *m* is a module and *name* accesses a name defined in *m*'s symbol "
"table. Module attributes can be assigned to.  (Note that the :keyword:"
"`import` statement is not, strictly speaking, an operation on a module "
"object; ``import foo`` does not require a module object named *foo* to "
"exist, rather it requires an (external) *definition* for a module named "
"*foo* somewhere.)"
msgstr ""
"ਮੋਡੀਊਲ ਉੱਤੇ ਇਕੱਲੀ ਖਾਸ ਕਾਰਵਾਈ attribute access ਹੈ: ``m.name``, ਜਿੱਥੇ *m* "
"ਇੱਕ module ਹੈ ਅਤੇ *name* ਉਸ ਦੇ symbol table ਵਿੱਚ ਪਰਿਭਾਸ਼ਿਤ ਨਾਮ ਤੱਕ ਪਹੁੰਚ "
"ਕਰਦਾ ਹੈ। Module attributes ਨੂੰ assign ਵੀ ਕੀਤਾ ਜਾ ਸਕਦਾ ਹੈ। (ਧਿਆਨ ਦਿਓ ਕਿ "
":keyword:`import` statement ਸਖ਼ਤ ਅਰਥਾਂ ਵਿੱਚ module object ਉੱਤੇ operation "
"ਨਹੀਂ ਹੈ; ``import foo`` ਲਈ *foo* ਨਾਮ ਦਾ module object ਮੌਜੂਦ ਹੋਣਾ ਲਾਜ਼ਮੀ "
"ਨਹੀਂ, ਸਗੋਂ ਕਿਤੇ ਨਾ ਕਿਤੇ *foo* ਨਾਮ ਦੇ module ਦੀ (external) ਪਰਿਭਾਸ਼ਾ ਹੋਣੀ "
"ਲੋੜੀਂਦੀ ਹੈ।)"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6242
msgid ""
"A special attribute of every module is :attr:`~object.__dict__`. This is the "
"dictionary containing the module's symbol table. Modifying this dictionary "
"will actually change the module's symbol table, but direct assignment to "
"the :attr:`~object.__dict__` attribute is not possible (you can write ``m."
"__dict__['a'] = 1``, which defines ``m.a`` to be ``1``, but you can't write "
"``m.__dict__ = {}``).  Modifying :attr:`~object.__dict__` directly is not "
"recommended."
msgstr ""
"ਹਰ module ਦਾ ਇੱਕ ਖਾਸ attribute :attr:`~object.__dict__` ਹੁੰਦਾ ਹੈ। ਇਹ ਉਹ "
"dictionary ਹੈ ਜਿਸ ਵਿੱਚ module ਦਾ symbol table ਹੁੰਦਾ ਹੈ। ਇਸ dictionary ਨੂੰ "
"ਬਦਲਣ ਨਾਲ module ਦਾ symbol table ਵੀ ਬਦਲ ਜਾਂਦਾ ਹੈ, ਪਰ "
":attr:`~object.__dict__` attribute ਨੂੰ ਸਿੱਧਾ assign ਨਹੀਂ ਕੀਤਾ ਜਾ ਸਕਦਾ "
"(ਤੁਸੀਂ ``m.__dict__['a'] = 1`` ਲਿਖ ਸਕਦੇ ਹੋ, ਜਿਸ ਨਾਲ ``m.a`` ਦੀ value ``1`` "
"ਹੋ ਜਾਂਦੀ ਹੈ, ਪਰ ``m.__dict__ = {}`` ਨਹੀਂ ਲਿਖ ਸਕਦੇ)। "
":attr:`~object.__dict__` ਨੂੰ ਸਿੱਧੇ ਤੌਰ 'ਤੇ ਬਦਲਣਾ ਸਿਫ਼ਾਰਸ਼ੀ ਨਹੀਂ ਹੈ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6250
msgid ""
"Modules built into the interpreter are written like this: ``<module "
"'sys' (built-in)>``.  If loaded from a file, they are written as ``<module "
"'os' from '/usr/local/lib/pythonX.Y/os.pyc'>``."
msgstr ""
"Interpreter ਵਿੱਚ built-in modules ਇਸ ਤਰ੍ਹਾਂ ਦਰਸਾਏ ਜਾਂਦੇ ਹਨ: "
"``<module 'sys' (built-in)>``। ਜੇਕਰ ਉਹ ਕਿਸੇ ਫਾਇਲ ਤੋਂ ਲੋਡ ਕੀਤੇ ਗਏ ਹੋਣ, ਤਾਂ "
"ਉਹ ਇਸ ਤਰ੍ਹਾਂ ਦਰਸਾਏ ਜਾਂਦੇ ਹਨ: "
"``<module 'os' from '/usr/local/lib/pythonX.Y/os.pyc'>``।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6258
msgid "Classes and Class Instances"
msgstr "Classes ਅਤੇ Class Instances"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6260
msgid "See :ref:`objects` and :ref:`class` for these."
msgstr "ਇਨ੍ਹਾਂ ਲਈ :ref:`objects` ਅਤੇ :ref:`class` ਵੇਖੋ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6266
msgid "Functions"
msgstr "Functions"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6268
msgid ""
"Function objects are created by function definitions.  The only operation on "
"a function object is to call it: ``func(argument-list)``."
msgstr ""
"Function objects, function definitions ਦੁਆਰਾ ਬਣਾਏ ਜਾਂਦੇ ਹਨ। Function object "
"ਉੱਤੇ ਮੁੱਖ operation ਉਸਨੂੰ call ਕਰਨਾ ਹੈ: ``func(argument-list)``।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6271
msgid ""
"There are really two flavors of function objects: built-in functions and "
"user-defined functions.  Both support the same operation (to call the "
"function), but the implementation is different, hence the different object "
"types."
msgstr ""
"ਅਸਲ ਵਿੱਚ function objects ਦੀਆਂ ਦੋ ਕਿਸਮਾਂ ਹੁੰਦੀਆਂ ਹਨ: built-in functions "
"ਅਤੇ user-defined functions। ਦੋਵੇਂ ਇੱਕੋ operation (function ਨੂੰ call ਕਰਨਾ) "
"ਦਾ ਸਮਰਥਨ ਕਰਦੇ ਹਨ, ਪਰ ਉਨ੍ਹਾਂ ਦੀ implementation ਵੱਖਰੀ ਹੁੰਦੀ ਹੈ, ਇਸ ਲਈ object "
"types ਵੀ ਵੱਖਰੇ ਹੁੰਦੇ ਹਨ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6275
msgid "See :ref:`function` for more information."
msgstr "ਹੋਰ ਜਾਣਕਾਰੀ ਲਈ :ref:`function` ਵੇਖੋ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6281
msgid "Methods"
msgstr "Methods"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6285
msgid ""
"Methods are functions that are called using the attribute notation. There "
"are two flavors: :ref:`built-in methods <builtin-methods>` (such as :meth:"
"`~list.append` on lists) and :ref:`class instance method <instance-"
"methods>`. Built-in methods are described with the types that support them."
msgstr ""
"Methods ਉਹ functions ਹਨ ਜਿਨ੍ਹਾਂ ਨੂੰ attribute notation ਰਾਹੀਂ call ਕੀਤਾ "
"ਜਾਂਦਾ ਹੈ। ਇਨ੍ਹਾਂ ਦੀਆਂ ਦੋ ਕਿਸਮਾਂ ਹਨ: :ref:`built-in methods "
"<builtin-methods>` (ਜਿਵੇਂ lists ਉੱਤੇ :meth:`~list.append`) ਅਤੇ "
":ref:`class instance methods <instance-methods>`। Built-in methods ਦਾ "
"ਵਰਣਨ ਉਹਨਾਂ ਕਿਸਮਾਂ ਦੇ ਨਾਲ ਕੀਤਾ ਜਾਂਦਾ ਹੈ ਜੋ ਉਨ੍ਹਾਂ ਦਾ ਸਮਰਥਨ ਕਰਦੀਆਂ ਹਨ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6291
msgid ""
"If you access a method (a function defined in a class namespace) through an "
"instance, you get a special object: a :dfn:`bound method` (also called :ref:"
"`instance method <instance-methods>`) object. When called, it will add the "
"``self`` argument to the argument list.  Bound methods have two special read-"
"only attributes: :attr:`m.__self__ <method.__self__>` is the object on which "
"the method operates, and :attr:`m.__func__ <method.__func__>` is the "
"function implementing the method.  Calling ``m(arg-1, arg-2, ..., arg-n)`` "
"is completely equivalent to calling ``m.__func__(m.__self__, arg-1, "
"arg-2, ..., arg-n)``."
msgstr ""
"ਜੇ ਤੁਸੀਂ ਕਿਸੇ instance ਰਾਹੀਂ method (class namespace ਵਿੱਚ ਪਰਿਭਾਸ਼ਿਤ function) "
"ਤੱਕ ਪਹੁੰਚ ਕਰਦੇ ਹੋ, ਤਾਂ ਤੁਹਾਨੂੰ ਇੱਕ ਖਾਸ object ਮਿਲਦਾ ਹੈ: :dfn:`bound method` "
"(ਜਿਸਨੂੰ :ref:`instance method <instance-methods>` ਵੀ ਕਿਹਾ ਜਾਂਦਾ ਹੈ)। "
"Call ਕਰਨ ਸਮੇਂ ਇਹ argument list ਵਿੱਚ ``self`` argument ਆਪਣੇ ਆਪ ਜੋੜ ਦਿੰਦਾ ਹੈ। "
"Bound methods ਦੇ ਦੋ ਖਾਸ read-only attributes ਹੁੰਦੇ ਹਨ: "
":attr:`m.__self__ <method.__self__>` ਉਹ object ਹੈ ਜਿਸ ਉੱਤੇ method ਕੰਮ "
"ਕਰਦੀ ਹੈ, ਅਤੇ :attr:`m.__func__ <method.__func__>` ਉਹ function ਹੈ ਜੋ "
"method ਨੂੰ ਲਾਗੂ ਕਰਦਾ ਹੈ। ``m(arg-1, arg-2, ..., arg-n)`` ਨੂੰ call ਕਰਨਾ "
"ਪੂਰੀ ਤਰ੍ਹਾਂ ``m.__func__(m.__self__, arg-1, arg-2, ..., arg-n)`` ਨੂੰ call "
"ਕਰਨ ਦੇ ਬਰਾਬਰ ਹੈ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6302
msgid ""
"Like :ref:`function objects <user-defined-funcs>`, bound method objects "
"support getting arbitrary attributes.  However, since method attributes are "
"actually stored on the underlying function object (:attr:`method.__func__`), "
"setting method attributes on bound methods is disallowed.  Attempting to set "
"an attribute on a method results in an :exc:`AttributeError` being raised.  "
"In order to set a method attribute, you need to explicitly set it on the "
"underlying function object:"
msgstr ""
":ref:`function objects <user-defined-funcs>` ਵਾਂਗ, bound method objects "
"ਤੋਂ arbitrary attributes ਪ੍ਰਾਪਤ ਕੀਤੇ ਜਾ ਸਕਦੇ ਹਨ। ਹਾਲਾਂਕਿ, method "
"attributes ਅਸਲ ਵਿੱਚ underlying function object "
"(:attr:`method.__func__`) ਉੱਤੇ ਸਟੋਰ ਹੁੰਦੇ ਹਨ, ਇਸ ਲਈ bound methods ਉੱਤੇ "
"method attributes ਸੈੱਟ ਕਰਨ ਦੀ ਆਗਿਆ ਨਹੀਂ ਹੁੰਦੀ। ਕਿਸੇ method ਉੱਤੇ attribute "
"ਸੈੱਟ ਕਰਨ ਦੀ ਕੋਸ਼ਿਸ਼ ਕਰਨ 'ਤੇ :exc:`AttributeError` ਉੱਠਦੀ ਹੈ। Method "
"attribute ਸੈੱਟ ਕਰਨ ਲਈ, ਤੁਹਾਨੂੰ ਇਸਨੂੰ ਸਪਸ਼ਟ ਤੌਰ 'ਤੇ underlying function "
"object ਉੱਤੇ ਸੈੱਟ ਕਰਨਾ ਪਵੇਗਾ:"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6310
msgid ""
">>> class C:\n"
"...     def method(self):\n"
"...         pass\n"
"...\n"
">>> c = C()\n"
">>> c.method.whoami = 'my name is method'  # can't set on the method\n"
"Traceback (most recent call last):\n"
"  File \"<stdin>\", line 1, in <module>\n"
"AttributeError: 'method' object has no attribute 'whoami'\n"
">>> c.method.__func__.whoami = 'my name is method'\n"
">>> c.method.whoami\n"
"'my name is method'"
msgstr ""
">>> class C:\n"
"...     def method(self):\n"
"...         pass\n"
"...\n"
">>> c = C()\n"
">>> c.method.whoami = 'my name is method'  # can't set on the method\n"
"Traceback (most recent call last):\n"
"  File \"<stdin>\", line 1, in <module>\n"
"AttributeError: 'method' object has no attribute 'whoami'\n"
">>> c.method.__func__.whoami = 'my name is method'\n"
">>> c.method.whoami\n"
"'my name is method'"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6325
msgid "See :ref:`instance-methods` for more information."
msgstr "ਹੋਰ ਜਾਣਕਾਰੀ ਲਈ :ref:`instance-methods` ਵੇਖੋ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6333
msgid "Code Objects"
msgstr "Code Objects"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6339
msgid ""
"Code objects are used by the implementation to represent \"pseudo-compiled\" "
"executable Python code such as a function body. They differ from function "
"objects because they don't contain a reference to their global execution "
"environment.  Code objects are returned by the built-in :func:`compile` "
"function and can be extracted from function objects through their :attr:"
"`~function.__code__` attribute. See also the :mod:`code` module."
msgstr ""
"Code objects implementation ਦੁਆਰਾ \"pseudo-compiled\" executable Python code "
"(ਜਿਵੇਂ ਕਿਸੇ function ਦਾ body) ਨੂੰ ਦਰਸਾਉਣ ਲਈ ਵਰਤੇ ਜਾਂਦੇ ਹਨ। ਇਹ function "
"objects ਤੋਂ ਵੱਖਰੇ ਹੁੰਦੇ ਹਨ ਕਿਉਂਕਿ ਇਨ੍ਹਾਂ ਵਿੱਚ ਆਪਣੇ global execution "
"environment ਦਾ reference ਨਹੀਂ ਹੁੰਦਾ। Code objects built-in "
":func:`compile` function ਦੁਆਰਾ ਵਾਪਸ ਕੀਤੇ ਜਾਂਦੇ ਹਨ ਅਤੇ function objects "
"ਤੋਂ ਉਹਨਾਂ ਦੇ :attr:`~function.__code__` attribute ਰਾਹੀਂ ਪ੍ਰਾਪਤ ਕੀਤੇ ਜਾ "
"ਸਕਦੇ ਹਨ। :mod:`code` module ਵੀ ਵੇਖੋ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6346
msgid ""
"Accessing :attr:`~function.__code__` raises an :ref:`auditing event "
"<auditing>` ``object.__getattr__`` with arguments ``obj`` and ``\"__code__"
"\"``."
msgstr ""
":attr:`~function.__code__` ਤੱਕ ਪਹੁੰਚ ਕਰਨ 'ਤੇ ``obj`` ਅਤੇ ``\"__code__\"`` "
"arguments ਨਾਲ ਇੱਕ :ref:`auditing event <auditing>` "
"``object.__getattr__`` ਉੱਠਦਾ ਹੈ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6353
msgid ""
"A code object can be executed or evaluated by passing it (instead of a "
"source string) to the :func:`exec` or :func:`eval`  built-in functions."
msgstr ""
"ਕਿਸੇ code object ਨੂੰ (source string ਦੀ ਥਾਂ) :func:`exec` ਜਾਂ "
":func:`eval` built-in functions ਨੂੰ ਪਾਸ ਕਰਕੇ execute ਜਾਂ evaluate ਕੀਤਾ "
"ਜਾ ਸਕਦਾ ਹੈ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6356
msgid "See :ref:`types` for more information."
msgstr "ਹੋਰ ਜਾਣਕਾਰੀ ਲਈ :ref:`types` ਵੇਖੋ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6362
msgid "Type Objects"
msgstr "Type Objects"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6368
msgid ""
"Type objects represent the various object types.  An object's type is "
"accessed by the built-in function :func:`type`.  There are no special "
"operations on types.  The standard module :mod:`types` defines names for all "
"standard built-in types."
msgstr ""
"Type objects ਵੱਖ-ਵੱਖ object ਕਿਸਮਾਂ ਨੂੰ ਦਰਸਾਉਂਦੇ ਹਨ। ਕਿਸੇ object ਦੀ type "
"ਤੱਕ built-in function :func:`type` ਰਾਹੀਂ ਪਹੁੰਚ ਕੀਤੀ ਜਾਂਦੀ ਹੈ। Types ਉੱਤੇ "
"ਕੋਈ ਖਾਸ operations ਨਹੀਂ ਹੁੰਦੀਆਂ। Standard module :mod:`types` ਸਾਰੀਆਂ "
"ਮਿਆਰੀ built-in types ਲਈ ਨਾਮ ਪਰਿਭਾਸ਼ਿਤ ਕਰਦਾ ਹੈ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6373
msgid "Types are written like this: ``<class 'int'>``."
msgstr "Types ਨੂੰ ਇਸ ਤਰ੍ਹਾਂ ਲਿਖਿਆ ਜਾਂਦਾ ਹੈ: ``<class 'int'>``।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6379
msgid "The Null Object"
msgstr "Null Object"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6381
msgid ""
"This object is returned by functions that don't explicitly return a value.  "
"It supports no special operations.  There is exactly one null object, named "
"``None`` (a built-in name).  ``type(None)()`` produces the same singleton."
msgstr ""
"ਇਹ object ਉਹਨਾਂ functions ਦੁਆਰਾ ਵਾਪਸ ਕੀਤਾ ਜਾਂਦਾ ਹੈ ਜੋ ਸਪਸ਼ਟ ਤੌਰ 'ਤੇ ਕੋਈ "
"value return ਨਹੀਂ ਕਰਦੀਆਂ। ਇਹ ਕਿਸੇ ਖਾਸ operation ਦਾ ਸਮਰਥਨ ਨਹੀਂ ਕਰਦਾ। "
"ਕੇਵਲ ਇੱਕ ਹੀ null object ਹੁੰਦਾ ਹੈ, ਜਿਸਦਾ ਨਾਮ ``None`` (ਇੱਕ built-in ਨਾਮ) "
"ਹੈ। ``type(None)()`` ਵੀ ਇਹੀ singleton ਬਣਾਉਂਦਾ ਹੈ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6385
msgid "It is written as ``None``."
msgstr "ਇਸਨੂੰ ``None`` ਵਜੋਂ ਲਿਖਿਆ ਜਾਂਦਾ ਹੈ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6392
msgid "The Ellipsis Object"
msgstr "Ellipsis Object"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6394
msgid ""
"This object is commonly used to indicate that something is omitted. It "
"supports no special operations.  There is exactly one ellipsis object, "
"named :const:`Ellipsis` (a built-in name).  ``type(Ellipsis)()`` produces "
"the :const:`Ellipsis` singleton."
msgstr ""
"ਇਹ object ਆਮ ਤੌਰ 'ਤੇ ਇਹ ਦਰਸਾਉਣ ਲਈ ਵਰਤਿਆ ਜਾਂਦਾ ਹੈ ਕਿ ਕੁਝ ਛੱਡਿਆ ਗਿਆ ਹੈ। "
"ਇਹ ਕਿਸੇ ਖਾਸ operation ਦਾ ਸਮਰਥਨ ਨਹੀਂ ਕਰਦਾ। ਕੇਵਲ ਇੱਕ ਹੀ ellipsis object "
"ਹੁੰਦਾ ਹੈ, ਜਿਸਦਾ ਨਾਮ :const:`Ellipsis` (ਇੱਕ built-in ਨਾਮ) ਹੈ। "
"``type(Ellipsis)()`` :const:`Ellipsis` singleton ਬਣਾਉਂਦਾ ਹੈ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6399
msgid "It is written as ``Ellipsis`` or ``...``."
msgstr "ਇਸਨੂੰ ``Ellipsis`` ਜਾਂ ``...`` ਵਜੋਂ ਲਿਖਿਆ ਜਾਂਦਾ ਹੈ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6401
msgid ""
"In typical use, ``...`` as the ``Ellipsis`` object appears in a few "
"different places, for instance:"
msgstr ""
"ਆਮ ਵਰਤੋਂ ਵਿੱਚ ``Ellipsis`` object ਵਜੋਂ ``...`` ਕਈ ਵੱਖ-ਵੱਖ ਥਾਵਾਂ 'ਤੇ "
"ਦਿਖਾਈ ਦਿੰਦਾ ਹੈ, ਉਦਾਹਰਨ ਵਜੋਂ:"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6404
msgid ""
"In type annotations, such as :ref:`callable arguments <annotating-"
"callables>` or :ref:`tuple elements <annotating-tuples>`."
msgstr ""
"Type annotations ਵਿੱਚ, ਜਿਵੇਂ :ref:`callable arguments "
"<annotating-callables>` ਜਾਂ :ref:`tuple elements <annotating-tuples>`।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6407
msgid ""
"As the body of a function instead of a :ref:`pass statement <tut-pass>`."
msgstr ""
":ref:`pass statement <tut-pass>` ਦੀ ਥਾਂ ਕਿਸੇ function ਦੇ body ਵਜੋਂ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6409
msgid ""
"In third-party libraries, such as `Numpy's slicing and striding <https://"
"numpy.org/doc/stable/user/basics.indexing.html#slicing-and-striding>`_."
msgstr ""
"Third-party libraries ਵਿੱਚ, ਜਿਵੇਂ Numpy ਦੀ slicing ਅਤੇ striding।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6412
msgid ""
"Python also uses three dots in ways that are not ``Ellipsis`` objects, for "
"instance:"
msgstr ""
"Python ਤਿੰਨ dots ਨੂੰ ਕੁਝ ਅਜਿਹੇ ਤਰੀਕਿਆਂ ਨਾਲ ਵੀ ਵਰਤਦਾ ਹੈ ਜੋ ``Ellipsis`` "
"objects ਨਹੀਂ ਹੁੰਦੇ, ਉਦਾਹਰਨ ਵਜੋਂ:"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6414
msgid ""
"Doctest's :const:`ELLIPSIS <doctest.ELLIPSIS>`, as a pattern for missing "
"content."
msgstr ""
"ਗੁੰਮ ਸਮੱਗਰੀ ਲਈ pattern ਵਜੋਂ Doctest ਦਾ "
":const:`ELLIPSIS <doctest.ELLIPSIS>`।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6416
msgid ""
"The default Python prompt of the :term:`interactive` shell when partial "
"input is incomplete."
msgstr ""
":term:`interactive` shell ਦਾ ਮੂਲ Python prompt ਜਦੋਂ ਅਧੂਰਾ input ਪੂਰਾ ਨਹੀਂ "
"ਹੁੰਦਾ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6418
msgid ""
"Lastly, the Python documentation often uses three dots in conventional "
"English usage to mean omitted content, even in code examples that also use "
"them as the ``Ellipsis``."
msgstr ""
"ਅੰਤ ਵਿੱਚ, Python documentation ਅਕਸਰ ਰਵਾਇਤੀ ਅੰਗਰੇਜ਼ੀ ਵਰਤੋਂ ਅਨੁਸਾਰ ਤਿੰਨ dots "
"ਦਾ ਵਰਤੋਂ ਛੱਡੀ ਗਈ ਸਮੱਗਰੀ ਦਰਸਾਉਣ ਲਈ ਕਰਦੀ ਹੈ, ਇੱਥੋਂ ਤੱਕ ਕਿ ਉਹਨਾਂ code "
"examples ਵਿੱਚ ਵੀ ਜਿੱਥੇ ਇਹ ``Ellipsis`` ਵਜੋਂ ਵੀ ਵਰਤੇ ਜਾਂਦੇ ਹਨ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6426
msgid "The NotImplemented Object"
msgstr "NotImplemented Object"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6428
msgid ""
"This object is returned from comparisons and binary operations when they are "
"asked to operate on types they don't support. See :ref:`comparisons` for "
"more information.  There is exactly one :data:`NotImplemented` object. :code:"
"`type(NotImplemented)()` produces the singleton instance."
msgstr ""
"ਇਹ object comparisons ਅਤੇ binary operations ਤੋਂ ਉਸ ਵੇਲੇ ਵਾਪਸ ਕੀਤਾ ਜਾਂਦਾ "
"ਹੈ ਜਦੋਂ ਉਨ੍ਹਾਂ ਨੂੰ ਅਜਿਹੀਆਂ types ਉੱਤੇ ਕੰਮ ਕਰਨ ਲਈ ਕਿਹਾ ਜਾਂਦਾ ਹੈ ਜਿਨ੍ਹਾਂ ਦਾ "
"ਉਹ ਸਮਰਥਨ ਨਹੀਂ ਕਰਦੀਆਂ। ਹੋਰ ਜਾਣਕਾਰੀ ਲਈ :ref:`comparisons` ਵੇਖੋ। "
"ਕੇਵਲ ਇੱਕ ਹੀ :data:`NotImplemented` object ਹੁੰਦਾ ਹੈ। "
":code:`type(NotImplemented)()` ਇਸ singleton instance ਨੂੰ ਬਣਾਉਂਦਾ ਹੈ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6433
msgid "It is written as :code:`NotImplemented`."
msgstr "ਇਸਨੂੰ :code:`NotImplemented` ਵਜੋਂ ਲਿਖਿਆ ਜਾਂਦਾ ਹੈ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6439
msgid "Internal Objects"
msgstr "Internal Objects"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6441
msgid ""
"See :ref:`types` for this information.  It describes :ref:`stack frame "
"objects <frame-objects>`, :ref:`traceback objects <traceback-objects>`, and "
"slice objects."
msgstr ""
"ਇਸ ਜਾਣਕਾਰੀ ਲਈ :ref:`types` ਵੇਖੋ। ਇਸ ਵਿੱਚ "
":ref:`stack frame objects <frame-objects>`, "
":ref:`traceback objects <traceback-objects>` ਅਤੇ slice objects ਦਾ "
"ਵਰਣਨ ਹੈ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6449
msgid "Special Attributes"
msgstr "ਖਾਸ Attributes"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6451
msgid ""
"The implementation adds a few special read-only attributes to several object "
"types, where they are relevant.  Some of these are not reported by the :func:"
"`dir` built-in function."
msgstr ""
"Implementation ਕਈ object types ਵਿੱਚ, ਜਿੱਥੇ ਲਾਗੂ ਹੋਵੇ, ਕੁਝ ਖਾਸ read-only "
"attributes ਜੋੜਦੀ ਹੈ। ਇਨ੍ਹਾਂ ਵਿੱਚੋਂ ਕੁਝ :func:`dir` built-in function "
"ਦੁਆਰਾ ਨਹੀਂ ਦਿਖਾਏ ਜਾਂਦੇ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6458
msgid ""
"The name of the class, function, method, descriptor, or generator instance."
msgstr ""
"Class, function, method, descriptor ਜਾਂ generator instance ਦਾ ਨਾਮ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6464
msgid ""
"The :term:`qualified name` of the class, function, method, descriptor, or "
"generator instance."
msgstr ""
"Class, function, method, descriptor ਜਾਂ generator instance ਦਾ "
":term:`qualified name`।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6472
msgid "The name of the module in which a class or function was defined."
msgstr "ਉਸ module ਦਾ ਨਾਮ ਜਿਸ ਵਿੱਚ class ਜਾਂ function ਪਰਿਭਾਸ਼ਿਤ ਕੀਤੀ ਗਈ ਸੀ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6477
msgid ""
"The documentation string of a class or function, or ``None`` if undefined."
msgstr ""
"Class ਜਾਂ function ਦੀ documentation string, ਜਾਂ ਜੇ ਪਰਿਭਾਸ਼ਿਤ ਨਾ ਹੋਵੇ ਤਾਂ "
"``None``।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6482
msgid ""
"The :ref:`type parameters <type-params>` of generic classes, functions, and :"
"ref:`type aliases <type-aliases>`. For classes and functions that are not "
"generic, this will be an empty tuple."
msgstr ""
"Generic classes, functions ਅਤੇ :ref:`type aliases <type-aliases>` ਦੇ "
":ref:`type parameters <type-params>`। ਜਿਹੜੀਆਂ classes ਅਤੇ functions "
"generic ਨਹੀਂ ਹਨ, ਉਨ੍ਹਾਂ ਲਈ ਇਹ ਇੱਕ ਖਾਲੀ tuple ਹੋਵੇਗੀ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6492
msgid "Integer string conversion length limitation"
msgstr "Integer string conversion ਦੀ ਲੰਬਾਈ ਦੀ ਸੀਮਾ"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6494
msgid ""
"CPython has a global limit for converting between :class:`int` and :class:"
"`str` to mitigate denial of service attacks. This limit *only* applies to "
"decimal or other non-power-of-two number bases. Hexadecimal, octal, and "
"binary conversions are unlimited. The limit can be configured."
msgstr ""
"Denial of service ਹਮਲਿਆਂ ਨੂੰ ਘਟਾਉਣ ਲਈ CPython ਵਿੱਚ :class:`int` ਅਤੇ "
":class:`str` ਵਿਚਕਾਰ conversion ਲਈ ਇੱਕ global limit ਹੈ। ਇਹ limit *ਕੇਵਲ* "
"decimal ਜਾਂ ਹੋਰ non-power-of-two number bases ਉੱਤੇ ਲਾਗੂ ਹੁੰਦੀ ਹੈ। "
"Hexadecimal, octal ਅਤੇ binary conversions ਉੱਤੇ ਕੋਈ ਸੀਮਾ ਨਹੀਂ ਹੈ। "
"ਇਸ limit ਨੂੰ configure ਕੀਤਾ ਜਾ ਸਕਦਾ ਹੈ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6499
msgid ""
"The :class:`int` type in CPython is an arbitrary length number stored in "
"binary form (commonly known as a \"bignum\"). There exists no algorithm that "
"can convert a string to a binary integer or a binary integer to a string in "
"linear time, *unless* the base is a power of 2. Even the best known "
"algorithms for base 10 have sub-quadratic complexity. Converting a large "
"value such as ``int('1' * 500_000)`` can take over a second on a fast CPU."
msgstr ""
"CPython ਵਿੱਚ :class:`int` ਇੱਕ arbitrary length number ਹੁੰਦਾ ਹੈ ਜੋ binary "
"ਰੂਪ ਵਿੱਚ ਸਟੋਰ ਕੀਤਾ ਜਾਂਦਾ ਹੈ (ਜਿਸਨੂੰ ਆਮ ਤੌਰ 'ਤੇ \"bignum\" ਕਿਹਾ ਜਾਂਦਾ ਹੈ)। "
"ਕੋਈ ਅਜਿਹਾ algorithm ਮੌਜੂਦ ਨਹੀਂ ਜੋ string ਨੂੰ binary integer ਜਾਂ binary "
"integer ਨੂੰ string ਵਿੱਚ linear time ਵਿੱਚ ਬਦਲ ਸਕੇ, *ਜਦ ਤੱਕ* base 2 ਦੀ "
"power ਨਾ ਹੋਵੇ। Base 10 ਲਈ ਸਭ ਤੋਂ ਵਧੀਆ ਜਾਣੇ-ਪਛਾਣੇ algorithms ਵੀ "
"sub-quadratic complexity ਰੱਖਦੇ ਹਨ। ``int('1' * 500_000)`` ਵਰਗੀ ਵੱਡੀ "
"value ਨੂੰ convert ਕਰਨ ਵਿੱਚ ਇੱਕ ਤੇਜ਼ CPU ਉੱਤੇ ਵੀ ਇੱਕ ਸਕਿੰਟ ਤੋਂ ਵੱਧ ਸਮਾਂ ਲੱਗ "
"ਸਕਦਾ ਹੈ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6506
msgid ""
"Limiting conversion size offers a practical way to avoid :cve:`2020-10735`."
msgstr ""
"Conversion ਦੇ ਆਕਾਰ ਨੂੰ ਸੀਮਿਤ ਕਰਨਾ :cve:`2020-10735` ਤੋਂ ਬਚਣ ਦਾ ਇੱਕ "
"ਵਿਹਾਰਕ ਤਰੀਕਾ ਹੈ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6508
msgid ""
"The limit is applied to the number of digit characters in the input or "
"output string when a non-linear conversion algorithm would be involved.  "
"Underscores and the sign are not counted towards the limit."
msgstr ""
"ਜਦੋਂ ਕੋਈ non-linear conversion algorithm ਵਰਤਿਆ ਜਾਂਦਾ ਹੈ, ਤਾਂ ਇਹ limit "
"input ਜਾਂ output string ਵਿੱਚ digit characters ਦੀ ਗਿਣਤੀ ਉੱਤੇ ਲਾਗੂ ਹੁੰਦੀ ਹੈ। "
"Underscores ਅਤੇ sign ਨੂੰ ਇਸ limit ਵਿੱਚ ਨਹੀਂ ਗਿਣਿਆ ਜਾਂਦਾ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6512
msgid ""
"When an operation would exceed the limit, a :exc:`ValueError` is raised:"
msgstr ""
"ਜਦੋਂ ਕੋਈ operation ਇਸ limit ਤੋਂ ਵੱਧ ਜਾਂਦੀ ਹੈ, ਤਾਂ :exc:`ValueError` "
"ਉੱਠਾਈ ਜਾਂਦੀ ਹੈ:"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6514
msgid ""
">>> import sys\n"
">>> sys.set_int_max_str_digits(4300)  # Illustrative, this is the default.\n"
">>> _ = int('2' * 5432)\n"
"Traceback (most recent call last):\n"
"...\n"
"ValueError: Exceeds the limit (4300 digits) for integer string conversion: "
"value has 5432 digits; use sys.set_int_max_str_digits() to increase the "
"limit\n"
">>> i = int('2' * 4300)\n"
">>> len(str(i))\n"
"4300\n"
">>> i_squared = i*i\n"
">>> len(str(i_squared))\n"
"Traceback (most recent call last):\n"
"...\n"
"ValueError: Exceeds the limit (4300 digits) for integer string conversion; "
"use sys.set_int_max_str_digits() to increase the limit\n"
">>> len(hex(i_squared))\n"
"7144\n"
">>> assert int(hex(i_squared), base=16) == i*i  # Hexadecimal is unlimited."
msgstr ""
">>> import sys\n"
">>> sys.set_int_max_str_digits(4300)  # Illustrative, this is the default.\n"
">>> _ = int('2' * 5432)\n"
"Traceback (most recent call last):\n"
"...\n"
"ValueError: Exceeds the limit (4300 digits) for integer string conversion: "
"value has 5432 digits; use sys.set_int_max_str_digits() to increase the "
"limit\n"
">>> i = int('2' * 4300)\n"
">>> len(str(i))\n"
"4300\n"
">>> i_squared = i*i\n"
">>> len(str(i_squared))\n"
"Traceback (most recent call last):\n"
"...\n"
"ValueError: Exceeds the limit (4300 digits) for integer string conversion; "
"use sys.set_int_max_str_digits() to increase the limit\n"
">>> len(hex(i_squared))\n"
"7144\n"
">>> assert int(hex(i_squared), base=16) == i*i  # Hexadecimal is unlimited."

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6534
msgid ""
"The default limit is 4300 digits as provided in :data:`sys.int_info."
"default_max_str_digits <sys.int_info>`. The lowest limit that can be "
"configured is 640 digits as provided in :data:`sys.int_info."
"str_digits_check_threshold <sys.int_info>`."
msgstr ""
"ਮੂਲ ਸੀਮਾ 4300 ਅੰਕਾਂ ਦੀ ਹੈ, ਜਿਵੇਂ :data:`sys.int_info."
"default_max_str_digits <sys.int_info>` ਵਿੱਚ ਦਿੱਤਾ ਗਿਆ ਹੈ। ਸੰਰਚਿਤ ਕੀਤੀ ਜਾ "
"ਸਕਣ ਵਾਲੀ ਸਭ ਤੋਂ ਘੱਟ ਸੀਮਾ 640 ਅੰਕਾਂ ਦੀ ਹੈ, ਜਿਵੇਂ :data:`sys.int_info."
"str_digits_check_threshold <sys.int_info>` ਵਿੱਚ ਦਿੱਤਾ ਗਿਆ ਹੈ।"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6539
msgid "Verification:"
msgstr "ਪੜਤਾਲ:"

#: ../../library/stdtypes.rst:6541
msgid ""
">>> import sys\n"
">>> assert sys.int_info.default_max_str_digits == 4300, sys.int_info\n"
">>> assert sys.int_info.str_digits_check_threshold == 640, sys.int_info\n"
">>> msg = int('578966293710682886880994035146873798396722250538762761564'\n"
"...           '9252925514383915483333812743580549779436104706260696366600'\n"
"...           '571186405732').to_bytes(53, 'big')\n"
"..."
msgstr ""
">>> import sys\n"
">>> assert sys.int_info.default_max_str_digits == 4300, sys.int_info\n"
">>> assert sys.int_info.str_digits_check_threshold == 640, sys.int_info\n"
">>> msg = int('578966293710682886880994035146873798396722250538762761564'\n"
"...           '9252925514383915483333812743580549779436104706260696366600'\n"
"...           '571186405732').to_bytes(53, 'big')\n"
"..."

